# AI design patterns

- Separate prompt templates from application code; version and test prompts independently.
- Use structured outputs (JSON schema, Pydantic, Zod) instead of parsing free-form LLM text.
- Implement guardrails: input validation, output filtering, max token limits, timeout handling.
- Cache LLM responses for deterministic, repeated queries (with TTL and cache key on prompt+model).
- Log prompts, completions, latency, token usage, and model version for every LLM call.
- Human-in-the-loop for high-stakes decisions; never fully automate without review paths.
- Fallback chain: primary model → cheaper/faster fallback → cached/default response.
- Evaluate with golden datasets before shipping prompt or model changes.
- Keep retrieval context minimal and relevant; more tokens ≠ better answers.
- Treat LLM outputs as untrusted input — validate before DB writes, code execution, or API calls.
